ENDEAVOR WIND II, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Endeavor Wind II, LLC ("Endeavor Wind II") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Endeavor Wind II generating facility ("Endeavor Wind II Facility").
Endeavor Wind II is a wind turbine generating facility located in Osceola County, Iowa. The Endeavor Wind II Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by ITC Midwest, LLC and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Endeavor Wind II's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Endeavor Wind II Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Endeavor Wind II's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Endeavor Wind II shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $289,707.69. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $24,142.31.
